[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_crkwx")
reagent_id = "H2SO3"
title = "Sulfurous acid"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]H₂SO₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]82 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State:[/cell][cell]Liquid (solution)[/cell]
[cell]Type:[/cell][cell]Weak acid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
SO₂ + H₂O → H₂SO₃
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Forms when sulfur dioxide dissolves in water.
• Unstable — can decompose back into SO₂ and water.
• Weaker than sulfuric acid (H₂SO₄).
[b]Where it is found[/b]
• In rainwater polluted with SO₂.
• In some industrial chemical processes.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Used in chemical reactions and industry.
• Related to sulfites, which are used as preservatives.
[b]Safety[/b]
Acidic and can irritate skin and eyes in concentrated solutions."
